olive oil
½ carrot
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag herbs
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet beef strips
1 packet mango chutney
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 tomato
¾ cup water

• Grate the carrot (see ingredients). Roughly chop tomato.
• In a medium saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
Cook carrot, stirring, until softened, 2 minutes.
• Add the water and chicken-style stock powder and bring to the boil.
• Add couscous, then stir to combine. Cover with a lid and remove from heat.
Set aside until water has absorbed, 5 minutes.
• Add tomato and baby spinach leaves and stir to combine.

Little cooks: Kids can help fluff up the couscous once the pan has cooled down!

• Pick and roughly chop herbs.
• In a small bowl, combine herbs and Greek-style yoghurt. Season with salt
and pepper. Set aside.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds,
tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a second small bowl.
• In a medium bowl, combine Mumbai spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil.
Add beef strips, season and toss to coat.

Little cooks: Take the lead by combining the ingredients for the yoghurt!

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, until browned and cooked
through, 1-2 minutes. Remove from heat, then add mango chutney. Toss
to coat.

• Divide leafy couscous between bowls.
• Top with mango-glazed Mumbai beef strips and toasted almonds.
• Serve with herby yoghurt. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the toasted almonds!